	<div class="position">
		<h3>Inventory Specialist</h3>
		<p><a href="mailto:bnorton@hayessoft.com?subject=Hayes Job Application - Inventory Specialist">email us your resume and cover letter</a></p>
		<p>The Inventory Specialist is a self-starting, effective communicator able to maintain client satisfaction across a variety of blended services. This position requires strong organizational skills, stellar attention to detail, and a contagious personality, as the focus will be geared toward a single project. The Inventory Specialist will work collaboratively with internal and external resources and act as the central information source for new asset management processes.</p>
		<div class="position_description"><p>
	<u><strong>Qualifications</strong></u><br />
	<br />
	&bull; Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree from an accredited university, preferably related to Business Administration.<br />
	&bull; Three (3) to five (5) years of work experience, with strong supervisor/management skills.<br />
	&bull; Demonstrated ability to provide stellar customer service.<br />
	&bull; Demonstrated ability to communicate and interface effectively across multiple channels, including but not limited to all districtwide members, internal project managers, and vendors.<br />
	&bull; Demonstrated strong written and verbal communication skills.<br />
	&bull; Excellent track record of sound decision making and follow through.<br />
	&bull; Ability to assess client needs throughout a project and manage those needs, expectations, and desired outcomes.<br />
	&bull; Strong organizational skills and attention to detail.<br />
	&bull; Advanced computer skills, ability to create reports/presentations using Excel, PowerPoint, etc.<br />
	&bull; Task-oriented self-starter with the ability to perform duties with a high level of accuracy.<br />
	&bull; Ability to meet established deadlines.<br />
	&bull; Ability to work flexible hours, including occasional nights and weekends.<br />
	&bull; Preferred &ndash; Related experience in inventory management, warehousing, and/or auditing.<br />
	<br />
	<u><strong>Basic Functions</strong></u></p>
<p>
	&bull; Assist in the implementation and completion of an asset management process across the 500+ campuses that make up the Chicago Public School system.<br />
	&bull; Serve as an on-site liaison for duration of project.<br />
	&bull; Effectively communicate and build relationships across multiple levels of the organization.<br />
	&bull; Assist with physical verification of assets throughout the district.<br />
	&bull; Assist with inventory planning procedures to mitigate risk during verification process.<br />
	&bull; Assist with the implementation of inventory control tracking software designed to manage assets.<br />
	&bull; Drive improvements and build efficiencies into the inventory control processes by working closely with stakeholders at all districtwide levels.<br />
	&bull; Maintain quality assurance throughout the project by performing and reviewing relevant assessments.<br />
	&bull; Actively participate in inventory control team initiatives to improve risk management procedures.<br />
	&bull; Assist with inventory control reporting and operations to promote effective utilization of processes and tools throughout asset management system.<br />
	&bull; Attend districtwide meetings on issues involving asset management policies and procedures.<br />
	&bull; Identify opportunities to further enhance asset management policy and procedures.<br />
	&bull; Perform all other tasks and duties as assigned.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	<strong>Benefits:&nbsp;</strong> <em>Excellent Employee Benefits and Amenities:</em> Medical/Dental Insurance &bull; Simple IRA with Employer Contribution &bull; Profit Sharing Plan &bull; 10+ days paid time off &bull; 10+ paid company holidays<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
</div>
